A1  - Teh, L S
A1  - Doherty, D G
A1  - Williams, B D
Y1  - 1994//
N2  - Antibodies to the ribosomal P protein are specific for SLE but their prevalence varies in different ethnic groups. In a group of Chinese SLE patients from Malaysia who have a high prevalence of this antibody, we have found an increased frequency of an uncharacterized HLA-DRB gene allele, DR16X, in patients who are positive for anti-P antibodies compared to antibody negative patients (31.3% vs 3.2%, P < 0.01, Pcorr not significant, relative risk = 13.6). DR16X has only been found in south east Asian populations and may be a genetic factor which influences the high prevalence of anti-P antibodies in Chinese.
