N2  - A 31-year-old women with polycystic ovary syndrome underwent dilatation and curettage (D&C) as part of her infertility workup. Pathologic examination revealed endometrial morular metaplasia without malignant potential. Follow-up D&C had no evidence of endometrial hyperplasia or carcinoma. The diagnostic difficulties and pathogenesis are discussed.
